The paper introduces an approach for searching structured data based on probabilistic programming and nonparametric Bayes, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also demonstrates applications to databases of US colleges, global macroeconomic indicators of public health, and classic cars, which further support these likely sub-categories.
